related_questions.snippet: Longer shoulder straps are generally in the 40-inch range and allow your bag to hang down near your hip when worn over your shoulder (depending on how tall you are, of course). For the petite person, this length can often be used to wear your bag across your body, or often referred to as the "cross body" position.
